courseDescription:
Project management skills and expertise are in great demand internationally. You can improve your project management skills and techniques and enhance your career prospects by studying Alison's Diploma in Project Management course. This course offers a comprehensive review of project management and the factors that need to be considered when planning a project. All of this is outlined in a clear and simple manner.

The course begins by explaining the various phases of the system development life cycle, including analysis, planning, design and evaluation. The course then describes project management methodology in detail, and guides you through project management tools such as Gantt and PERT charts. Next, the course describes the different types of documentation found in project management such as program, system, technical, paper-based, electronic and specialist user documentation that help to show how a project has been set up. 

Finally, the course goes through a project management case study where you can see the various phases of project management being carried out. This course will be of great interest to professionals working in businesses and organisations who manage projects and would like to improve their project management skills. It will also be of interest to learners who are considering project management as a career.

modules.name: Module
modules.description: This module introduces modern project management theory and practice. Learn about projects, project management, project context, key skills of a project manager, and project management knowledge areas.
topics: Key Skills of the Project Manager
Introduction to PM Knowledge Areas - Part 1
Introduction to PM Knowledge Areas - Part 2

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about project profiles from using a project profile, complex systems, and the factors of the Darnall-Preston Complexity Index (DPCI) structure which include the external, internal, technology and environmental factors.

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about project phases and organization. This includes an introduction to project phases, project organization and measuring organizational complexity.

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn about managing and meeting client expectations from including the client, understanding value and expectations, dealing with problems, nurturing a feeling of satisfaction.

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about working with individual and teams on projects from handling issues of trust, managing team meetings and types of teams, and creating a project culture.
topics: Working with Teams - Managing Team Meetings
Working with Teams - Types of Teams

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about communication technologies in projects. This module includes types of communication, types of software that are appropriate for projects of different levels of complexity, and strategies for sharing documents that can be edited by a team.

modules.name: Module
modules.details: Diploma in Modern Project Management - First Assessment
modules.description: You must score 80% or more to pass this assessment.
topics: Diploma in Modern Project Management - First Assessment

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about starting a project in this module from the process of project selection, evaluating the project scope, the project start-up phase, the alignment process, and the communications planning procedure.

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about project time management in this module from types of schedules, elements of time management, critical path and float, managing the schedule, and project scheduling software.

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about the strategies and means of estimating and managing project costs in modern project management in this module from estimating required project costs and managing the budget for projects.

modules.name: Module
modules.details: Introduction to Project Quality and Statistics
modules.description: Learn more about quality control in project management from project quality and statistics, development of quality as a competitive advantage, relevance of quality programs to project quality, planning and controlling project quality, and assuring quality.
topics: Development of Quality as a Competitive Advantage
Relevance of Quality Programs to Project Quality

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about risk in modern project management in this module from defining risk, the risk management process, analyzing project risk by phases, and project risk and the project complexity profile.
topics: Project Risk and the Project Complexity Profile

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about the procurement process in project management in this module from identifying the need for resources outside the organization, planning process for procurement, selecting the contract type, and the procurement process.
topics: Identifying the Need for Resources Outside the Organization

modules.name: Module
modules.description: Learn more about the closure phase of projects in modern project management in this module from procedures for closing out contracts, post-project review process,documents to be archived, and project closeout celebrations.
